---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Miller Trust Guide"
  description="About the author and editorial principles behind Miller Trust Guide. We are researchers, not attorneys."
>
  <article class="prose-content mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm James Whitfield. I built this site after spending weeks helping my own family member set up a Miller Trust.
      The free state-published templates were technically correct but operationally useless — they explained the form
      fields and stopped there. The attorneys quoted $1,500–$2,500 for what turned out to be a few hours of paperwork
      and a phone call to the bank. The gap between "free PDF that doesn't help" and "$2,000 attorney" is where most
      families get stuck. This site fills that gap.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm not an attorney. I'm a researcher who has now read every state Medicaid policy manual section that covers
      Qualified Income Trusts. I publish what I learned — the operational steps, the bank-account walkthroughs, the
      common denial reasons, the citations. I will not advise you on your specific situation; for that, you need a
      licensed elder-law attorney in your state. The state bar in your state has a referral service for low-cost
      initial consultations.
    </p>

    <p>
      I work anonymously. The state agency manuals are the authority and they do the talking. I do not maintain social
      media accounts under this name and I do not give phone interviews. The author byline is consistent across every
      page, every email, and every support reply because consistency is the most honest signal I can give that a real
      person is behind this work.
    </p>

    <h2>What we publish — and what we won't</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>State-specific operational guides built around publicly-published state QIT templates.</li>
      <li>Email support, limited to product, refund, and "we are not attorneys" questions.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Draft, host, or distribute trust instrument text. We link to the state's own .gov template.</li>
      <li>Customize a kit based on your family's situation. Every buyer in a given state receives the same kit.</li>
      <li>Give advice over phone, chat, or email about your specific situation. We do not have a phone number.</li>
      <li>Sell email addresses, share buyer data with attorneys, or run an affiliate / referral business.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:support@millertrustguide.com">support@millertrustguide.com</a> for product, refund, or
      kit-clarification questions. For advice on your specific situation, please contact a licensed elder-law attorney
      in your state — your state bar association maintains a referral service for low-cost initial consultations.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
